  "text": "The self-efficacy for personal-social skills questionnaire [CITATION_1] is an eight-item questionnaire to quantitatively assess the novice instructors' self-efficacy beliefs regarding their ability to teach personal and social skills (\"For each item, please rate how confident you are that you can teach that objective through physical activity programme.\" is followed by items, such as \"self-control\", \"respect for others\" and \"cooperation\"). Ratings are based on an 11-point Likert scale (0 = not confident at all and 10 = extremely confident).",
